The paper deals with improving the performance of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN) for object recognition tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The proposed method involves a non-iterative learning strategy, which could also fall under the category of optimization (cs.NE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions using natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze the experimental results, which could relate to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
